rComments: Michael Phelps is the best swimmer in the world. Usain Bolt is the best runner in the world. Y. Y. Chen is the best remote learning prof. If I could rate him a 10/5 on this website I would.

Y. Y. Chen is a national treasure. I took him during the first semester of the pandemic. He has adapted his lectures to remote learning better than any other prof I know. He created his own website to host recorded lectures, because he knows BrightSpace is a headache. Zoom class still sucks but Chen did the best a person could in the circumstances

Would highly recommend Chen to anyone. Great guy overall. Super understanding of his students needs and genuinely wants them to succeed. Very articulate and clear as to what his expectations are from students. Super accessible both in and out of class. 101% the best prof of my 1st year. No kidding - gives off a real zen vibe.
This is the nicest professor I've met in law school, always approachable after class. Definitely recommend.

Professor Chen is one of the nicest Professors at the University. He goes out of his way to ensure that his students aren't drowning in work. He spoonfeeds the readings to you in class, so it is best to record the lecture or type his words verbatim. Exam is 6-hours, and takes the full 6 hours. He hands you the law, you are grading on application.
